Using Git & GitHub
------------------

Done!


Using RVM
---------

* Installing the stable release of RVM and reloading the shell environment.
  This method installs RVM for the current user only, under ~/.rvm:

    $ bash -s stable < <(curl -s https://raw.github.com/wayneeseguin/rvm/master/binscripts/rvm-installer)
    $ source ~/.bash_profile

* To see a list of available Ruby interpreters:

    $ rvm list known

* Now install Ruby 1.9.3 and make this version the default for our environment:

    $ rvm install 1.9.3
    $ rvm list
    $ rvm use 1.9.3 --default
    $ rvm list


Installing Gems and Heroku
--------------------------

* Install heroku gem in the current active ruby. If you use the 'rvm' keyword you will
  need to specify the ruby version you want to install the gem to.

    $ gem install heroku

    # List installed gems
    $ gem list

    # Find the location of a library
    $ gem which heroku

    # Uninstall a gem
    $ gem uninstall heroku

    # More help
    $ gem help commands

* Uploading the public key to Heroku:

    $ heroku keys:add 


Installing Bundle
-----------------

    $ gem install bundle


